<br>
My only comment is this.  When someone creates a guild the guild name is soulbound to their account, as in, it stays there forever.   If this Raine was the original Guild leader of the Guild then they can come back and reclaim it at any time.<br>
<br>
This is worth a thought to all of the other Guilds out there where leadership was passed down from someone else at one point.  Are you 100% sure that the person who 'owns' your Guild is never going to either come back and reclaim their Guild or sell their account.  <br>
<br>
Be very careful.  It's happened to two guilds recently on Stormhammer and for this very reason we disbanded and reformed our own guild under a new name to ensure it's safety.<br>
<br>
It's still despicable nonetheless... /sigh<br>
