<br>
I know of who Cuellari was through a few stories from my sister dating way back to times in Crushbone (almost two years ago)  Cuellari was one of the very few people who drove my sister away by being a terrible person.  There was some big, ridiculous ordeal about Cuellari accusing my sister of trying to steal her husband because she kept smiling at him ~~~&gt;  =) or something as foolish as that.  (She smiles at EVERYONE like that, before anyone jumps to anything)  In short, Cuellari is not a nice person, and she is someone I would believe fully capable of the actions described.  She was enough of a bad thing to have my sister track her actions so that she could continue to avoid her in the future.<br>
<br>
I also, from the stories told, believe her to not only be one of the founding members of KotEW, but to have been their first and original leader.  I have found a few detached statements elsewhere to verify this information, but they are not strong enough to stand without more.<br>
<br>
I have two questions about this warning directed to Aailin (or someone else who might know):<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>First Question:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Can you offer any evidence for what happened other than the 'take my word for it' story we are given here.  No, I am not calling you a liar or accusing you of trying to give a skewed viewpoint on the matter, but as I understand, you are not in any direct way related to this situation.  You have no direct experience of any of this, and only know what you have been told by others.<br>
<br>
This would make your stance on the subject entirely hearsay.  I know you that it is accepted knowledge that you are a lawyer, so you know what this means for what has been said thus far.<br>
<br>
As it stands now, with no support from people involved, this is nothing more than a potential witch hunt.  For all we know (or you yourself) you have been given misinformation or misrepresented facts, or misunderstood facts, and you are relaying that information to us.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>To be blunt, unless you have a direct link to this situation, your words are nothing.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Sorry to bold it, but it seems to me that people need to understand this, because they appear to be jumping on a bandwagon based on nothing more than your words.<br>
<br>
I would really hope that people would rely on more than the accusations of one person who was not in any way involved before burning a 'witch'.  At least give the 'witch' her chance to defend herself.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Second question:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> How much do you know about the history of the guild and its people, and how do you know this information?  Is Fallguy the same person as Rasaoakleaf?  I have a reason to believe it is a possibility (could anyone verify or reject this with personal knowledge?)<br>
<br>
If they are the same person, it certainly adds a good bit of support to the claims made.<br>
<br>
Normally, I would not care about any of this.  But I know of Cuellari (again, one of perhaps three people in two years who were vile enough to drive my sister away) and feel that she is fully capable of being a terrible enough person to steal a guild.<br>
<br>
And second, the reason I made the speech about hearsay, is because when reading the original post, a red flag went off in my head that makes me question what happened.<br>
<br>
If Raile took control by claiming that Fallguy was gone from the game, the fact that Fallguy is back and petitioning should be enough to let the GMs know something.  This would be something so simple to attack in order to reveal the truth.  If he would switch leadership because someone gave him information about the leader being gone, why would he not switch it back when he finds direct proof that the information for leader change was false?<br>
<br>
Makes me think there is something we are not being told. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=toveebearwhisper>Tovee BearWhisper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/6/03 11:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3817.topic&index=38>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Raile and the Knights of the Ebon Wolf..</span><hr size=1> There is actually quite a bit of &quot;evidence&quot; on their boards:<br>
